      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">


            <h1 class="signature" translate="no">union(SetList :: [<a href="#t:set/1">set</a>(Element)])<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">Set</span></h1>




          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/stdlib/src/sets.erl#L534" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">


        <div class="specs">
          <h4 class="specs-title">Types</h4>

            <pre translate="no">Set = <a href="#t:set/1">set</a>(Element)</pre>

        </div>


<p>Returns the union of a list of sets.</p><p>The union of multiple sets is a new set that contains all the elements from
all sets, without duplicates.</p><h2 id="union/1-examples" class="section-heading"><a href="#union/1-examples" class="hover-link"><i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i></a><span class="text">Examples</span></h2><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="gp unselectable">1&gt; </span><span class="n">S0</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">from_list</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-1">(</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-2">[</span><span class="ss">a</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">b</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">c</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">d</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-2">]</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-1">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">2&gt; </span><span class="n">S1</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">from_list</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-3">(</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-4">[</span><span class="ss">d</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">e</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">f</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-4">]</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-3">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">3&gt; </span><span class="n">S2</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">from_list</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-5">(</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-6">[</span><span class="ss">q</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">r</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-6">]</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-5">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">4&gt; </span><span class="n">Sets</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-7">[</span><span class="n">S0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">S1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">S2</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-7">]</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">5&gt; </span><span class="n">Union</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">union</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-8">(</span><span class="n">Sets</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-8">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">6&gt; </span><span class="nc">lists</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">sort</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-9">(</span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">to_list</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-10">(</span><span class="n">Union</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-10">)</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-9">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-11">[</span><span class="ss">a</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">b</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">c</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">d</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">e</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">f</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">q</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">r</span><span class="p" data-group-id="7474931384-11">]</span></code></pre>
  </section>
</section>
<section class="detail" id="union/2">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#union/2" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">


            <h1 class="signature" translate="no">union(Set1 :: <a href="#t:set/1">set</a>(Element), Set2 :: <a href="#t:set/1">set</a>(Element))<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">Set3</span></h1>




          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/stdlib/src/sets.erl#L503" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">


        <div class="specs">
          <h4 class="specs-title">Types</h4>

            <pre translate="no">Set1 = Set2 = Set3 = <a href="#t:set/1">set</a>(Element)</pre>

        </div>


<p>Returns the union of <code class="inline">Set1</code> and <code class="inline">Set2</code>.</p><p>The union of two sets is a new set that contains all the elements from
both sets, without duplicates.</p><h2 id="union/2-examples" class="section-heading"><a href="#union/2-examples" class="hover-link"><i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i></a><span class="text">Examples</span></h2><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="gp unselectable">1&gt; </span><span class="n">S0</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">from_list</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-1">(</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-2">[</span><span class="ss">a</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">b</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">c</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">d</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-2">]</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-1">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">2&gt; </span><span class="n">S1</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">from_list</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-3">(</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-4">[</span><span class="ss">c</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">d</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">e</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="ss">f</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-4">]</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-3">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">3&gt; </span><span class="n">Union</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">sets</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">union</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-5">(</span><span class="n">S0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">S1</span><span class="p" data-group-id="5687627885-5">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
